<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1436,1888,2029]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis box="[207,462,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: The broadly triangular anal point with straight sides and pointed apex and with microtrichia and setae together with the posterior placement 0n the gonocoxite of the long and slightly curved inferior volsella will separate the male imago from other members of the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1436,1888,2029]" box="[207,1384,2005,2029]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis box="[207,327,2005,2029]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Etymology</emphasis>
: From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[516,570,2006,2029]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">teres</emphasis>
, rounded and 
<emphasis box="[731,816,2006,2029]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">cristata</emphasis>
, with keel, referring to the rounded crista dorsalis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" box="[151,368,158,182]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis box="[151,285,158,182]" italics="true" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Male imago</emphasis>
(n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
Total length 
<quantity box="[294,397,197,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.49" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="1.49">1.49 mm</quantity>
. Wing length 
<quantity box="[554,657,197,221]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.74">0.74 mm</quantity>
. Total length/wing length 2.01. Wing length/length of profemur 2.83. Coloration yellowish brown with dark brown vittae and markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[289,403,275,299]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="171.[151,250,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[361,1254,198,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-118@171.[230,1364,188,1776]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 62. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A—P. tobaduovicesima Kikuchi &amp; Sasa (From Kikuchi &amp; Sasa, 1990). B–G. P.tericristata sp. n., B—head; C—wing; D—thorax; E—virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288469/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 62 B</figureCitation>
). AR 0.73. Terminal flagellomere 201 µm long, no strong apical seta. Temporal setae 5, consisting of 2 inner verticals and 2 outer verticals; no postorbitals. Tentorium 82 µm long, 14 µm wide. Cibarial pump and stipes as in 
<figureCitation box="[408,521,353,377]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="171.[151,250,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[361,1254,198,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-118@171.[230,1364,188,1776]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 62. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A—P. tobaduovicesima Kikuchi &amp; Sasa (From Kikuchi &amp; Sasa, 1990). B–G. P.tericristata sp. n., B—head; C—wing; D—thorax; E—virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288469/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 62 D</figureCitation>
. Stipes 78 µm long, 25 µm wide. Palpomere lengths (in µm): 14, 25, 42, 55,73. Third palpomere with 4 pin-shaped sensilla clavata.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[307,418,431,455]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="171.[151,250,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[361,1254,198,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-118@171.[230,1364,188,1776]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 62. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A—P. tobaduovicesima Kikuchi &amp; Sasa (From Kikuchi &amp; Sasa, 1990). B–G. P.tericristata sp. n., B—head; C—wing; D—thorax; E—virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288469/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 62 D</figureCitation>
). Antepronotum with 1 lateral setae. Dorsocentrals 12, acrostichals 2, prealars 4. Scutellum with 4 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[287,393,509,533]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="171.[151,250,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[361,1254,198,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-118@171.[230,1364,188,1776]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 62. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A—P. tobaduovicesima Kikuchi &amp; Sasa (From Kikuchi &amp; Sasa, 1990). B–G. P.tericristata sp. n., B—head; C—wing; D—thorax; E—virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288469/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 62 C</figureCitation>
). VR 1.67, postcubitus simple. Anal lobe reduced, but wing not cuneiform. 
<collectingRegion box="[1220,1282,509,533]" country="Tanzania" name="Pwani" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Costa</collectingRegion>
not extended. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[169,193,563,577]" fontSize="6" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">4+5</subScript>
ending far proximal to apex of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[561,585,563,577]" fontSize="6" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">3+4</subScript>
; Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[631,639,563,577]" fontSize="6" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">1</subScript>
straight. Brachiolum with 1 seta, other veins bare.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Legs. Spur of front tibia 30 µm long, spurs of middle tibia broken, of hind tibia 37 µm and 25 µm long. Width at apex of front and middle tibiae 17–18 µm, of hind tibia 29 µm. Comb of 12 setae, 21–34 µm long. All tarsi lost. Lengths (in µm) of front to hind femur: 261, 306, 306; of front to hind tibiae: 297, 302, 306.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="172.[151,1437,158,853]" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">
Hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[374,486,711,735]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="171.[151,250,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[361,1254,198,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-118@171.[230,1364,188,1776]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 62. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A—P. tobaduovicesima Kikuchi &amp; Sasa (From Kikuchi &amp; Sasa, 1990). B–G. P.tericristata sp. n., B—head; C—wing; D—thorax; E—virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288469/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 62 F</figureCitation>
). Anal point 18 µm long, with about 8 lateral setae; laterosternite IX with 3 setae. Phallapodeme 49 µm long; transverse sternapodeme 27 µm long. Virga (
<figureCitation box="[953,1058,750,774]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="171.[151,250,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[361,1254,198,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-118@171.[230,1364,188,1776]" captionTargetPageId="171" captionText="FIGURE 62. Pseudosmittia spp., male. A—P. tobaduovicesima Kikuchi &amp; Sasa (From Kikuchi &amp; Sasa, 1990). B–G. P.tericristata sp. n., B—head; C—wing; D—thorax; E—virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288469/files/figure.png" pageId="172" pageNumber="173">Fig. 62 E</figureCitation>
) 21 µm long. Gonocoxite 114 µm long, with 25 µm long digitiform inferior volsella reaching to 0.82 gonocoxite length. Gonostylus 45 µm long, with weak rounded preapical crista dorsalis and megaseta only 3 µm long; HR 2.56, HV 3.30.
</paragraph>
